{"type":"message","id":"fd8e5eb0","parentId":"93ed0099","timestamp":"2026-04-13T04:48:38.628Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that my push to `fix/auth-registration-ui` is now on remote. The develop pipeline (2448034759) was the one that failed before my push. The pipeline might re-trigger now that develop has my fix. But my push to `fix/auth-registration-ui` should also trigger a separate pipeline.\n\nLet me just check the GitLab pipeline API to see if there's a new pipeline for my branch. Actually, I notice there's no new pipeline in the list. This could be because GitLab hasn't processed the push yet, or because the push to `fix/auth-registration-ui` was already merged into develop (so there's no new work to do there).\n \nLooking at the failed pipeline, it shows commit `a8cf208` which is the merge commit of my MR into develop. That was before my fix. Now that my fix is on develop, the pipeline should re-run automatically. GitLab's \"retry\" mechanism might have already kicked in, so I should check if there's a new pipeline running or if I need to manually trigger one.\n\nLet me pull the latest state from the remote to see if a new pipeline has been created.","thinkingSignature":"de3c3ad70cb0892f08ea6b65d8cf2485feedad6e5a77512d2c1b7132c5a25952"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_w0l1kyp34exn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-fe && git fetch origin && git log origin/develop --oneline -3","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":460,"output":308,"cacheRead":61601,"cacheWrite":3894,"totalTokens":66263,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776055711322,"responseId":"062ba8a0e3bb0a8981a4aef317a71140"}}
