{"type":"message","id":"41284f38","parentId":"484a4782","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:05:48.779Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lead is saying the :8686/api/v1/license-categories URL is the URL when they deployed locally (not the remote server). So the issue is about their local deployment, not the CI/CD remote deployment.\n\nThe error URL `http://103.253.21.139:8686/api/v1/license-categories` - this is the NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL pointing to 103.253.21.139:8686 (not 5002). But the `.env.local` shows port 5002... unless Lead deployed with a different `.env` file or the deployment used a different environment.\n\nWait - the URL in the error is `:8686` which could mean the frontend is calling relative to its own port? No, that's not right either.\n\n\nActually, I think I see it now. The frontend is making an API call to `http://103.253.21.139:8686/api/v1/license-categories`, but `.env.local` specifies port 5002, not 8686. Either the deployment used a different environment file, or the API_URL variable got overridden somewhere during the deployment process.\n\nThe real problem is likely that `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` was set to `http://103.253.21.139:8686/api/v1` when the image was built, but the backend is actually running on port 5002. This would happen if `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` wasn't properly configured in the CI/CD variables or docker-compose setup before deployment, causing the fallback to use an incorrect port or hostname.\n\nLooking at the deployment script, it's running `docker compose up -d --build` after pulling from Git, but without passing the `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` environment variable to the build process. So even though the local `.env.local` has the correct port 5002, the deployed image might have been built without that variable set, defaulting to `http://127.0.0.1:5002/api/v1` instead.\n\nThe URL error shows port 8686, which suggests either the API URL in the deployed environment is pointing to port 8686, or the deployed frontend is somehow making requests to that port directly. The `:8686` could also be coming from a NEXT_PUBLIC_BASE_URL or similar variable that's configured differently in the deployed environment versus local.\n\nI think the core issue is that the docker-compose setup doesn't specify the API URL, so the built image is using a default that doesn't match where the backend actually runs. The solution would be to pass the correct NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL environment variable when running docker-compose up.","thinkingSignature":"7e604f150919e33e1b893d221287eb553ebed4259b49a36c2409635e28491ac8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_31fb31fy8f1t_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" \"http://103.253.21.139:8686/api/v1/license-categories\" --connect-timeout 5 2>&1","timeout":8}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":608,"cacheRead":98144,"cacheWrite":895,"totalTokens":99647,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776056729380,"responseId":"062bac9bcb041590aea2f9c210ee63d1"}}
