{"type":"message","id":"bc2f1801","parentId":"b0c9c052","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:17:47.657Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The problem is the order of rules in .gitignore. Git processes patterns in order. `.env*` comes after `!.env.production` so it re-ignores it. I need to put `.env*` first, then `!.env.production` after it.\n\nLet me fix this properly:\n```\n# env files (can opt-in for committing if needed)\n.env*\n!.env.production\n```\nThis way: `.env*` ignores → then `!.env.production` un-ignores it specifically.","thinkingSignature":"9bca9838ea8382f9ccbf36ec9d8e461a21f41500602f33738ae8f183efcf53e3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_svijel7cv133_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-fe && sed -i '33,35d' .gitignore && sed -i '32 a\\# env files (can opt-in for committing if needed)\\n.env*\\n!.env.production' .gitignore && sed -n '31,38p' .gitignore && git check-ignore -v .env.production"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":183,"output":224,"cacheRead":107650,"cacheWrite":386,"totalTokens":108443,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776057457027,"responseId":"062baf753898802d3df5224e49ab666f"}}
