{"type":"message","id":"ed26cf45","parentId":"1308dbfc","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:20:32.678Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the BE has 11 local commits that include the `license-categories` CRUD API, but those haven't been pushed to remote. The remote has 2 commits that BE local doesn't have (data isolation for teachers).\n\nSo the solution is to push the BE changes to remote. But per Lead's new rule, I should NOT push directly to `develop`. I need to create a feature branch.\n\nActually wait - the local BE already has the `license-categories` API. I need to:1. Create a feature branch from `develop` (or from current local HEAD?) \n2. The local BE is ahead of remote by 11 commits AND behind remote by 2 commits\n\n\n3. Create a feature branch for the `license-categories` feature\n4. Push that branch to remote\n5. Create MR\n\nLet me create the feature branch and push it. Actually, the commits I want are the ones about `license-categories` CRUD. Looking at the local commits:- `9c331b2` - feat(settings): add license-categories CRUD API + load from database- The rest are about notifications system\n\nLet me create a branch from current position and push it. Wait, Lead said \"bạn làm hỏng hệ thống của tôi rồi, bỏ ngay file .env.production\" - this was about FE, not BE. Lead wanted me to remove the .env.production file from FE (which I did), and now Lead is clarifying the BE issue. So for BE, I need to create a feature branch from the current local position and push it with the `license-categories` changes, then create a merge request for review.","thinkingSignature":"94c77b579ccf113e90e6a59a23c697004fc7155c9db28b64344aeab49d225c76"},{"type":"text","text":"Đúng rồi! BE local có API `license-categories` nhưng chưa push lên remote. Mình tạo feature branch để Lead review:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bs5dsmdqm2uq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bo