{"type":"message","id":"f57930a1","parentId":"a764d290","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:24:08.239Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The job failed after only 39 seconds. Let me try to retry the pipeline. First, let me check if I can retry it.Actually, the better fix is to update the CI script to clear node_modules before yarn install. Let me create a fix branch and push it.\n\nActually, looking at the CI logs more carefully:```\nyarn install --frozen-lockfile --cache-folder .yarn-cache\n```\nThis installs with frozen lockfile. The issue might be that the cache has `node_modules` that doesn't include eslint (because eslint was added later), and `yarn install --frozen-lockfile` might be skipping because node_modules already exists.\n\n\nThe real solution is to force a fresh install by deleting the cached node_modules before running yarn, or use the `--frozen-lockfile` flag which guarantees a clean install from scratch.","thinkingSignature":"e7932685df65f7d4d627c7a33bca2152cd143bfa9b43452dbdc1f95aac2f4711"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_968yp6540qu7_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/.gitlab-ci.yml","edits":[{"oldText":"  script:\n    - yarn install --frozen-lockfile --cache-folder .yarn-cache\n    - yarn lint","newText":"  script:\n    - yarn install --frozen-lockfile --cache-folder .yarn-cache\n    - node node_modules/.bin/eslint 'src/**/*.ts' --no-warn-ignored || node_modules/eslint/bin/eslint.js 'src/**/*.ts' --no-warn-ignored"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":132,"output":329,"cacheRead":119447,"cacheWrite":1017,"totalTokens":120925,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776057840001,"responseId":"062bb0f1c478b247dc10e015c0416583"}}
