{"type":"message","id":"557ff03a","parentId":"d7d17c4f","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:09:37.936Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lead is getting a CORS error. The FE is trying to call `http://103.253.21.98:8686/api/v1/auth/me` but the CORS policy is blocking it. \n\nWait, the FE is at `http://103.253.21.98:6868` and trying to call the BE at `http://103.253.21.98:8686`. These are different ports. CORS is blocking cross-origin requests.\n\nBut wait, this is a new error after deployment. The issue might be:\n1. The BE CORS configuration doesn't allow the FE origin\n2. The BE is running on a different port than expected\n\nActually, looking at the error - the BE port is `:8686` but earlier we saw the BE running on `:5002`. \n\nSo the production BE is deployed on port 8686, while the dev environment uses 5002, and the FE on 6868 is trying to make requests to the BE API. The CORS configuration on the BE needs to allow the FE's origin to enable these cross-origin requests.","thinkingSignature":"8d52f90a43e6deaca7887d631d6df36714128427ddbb65cf1f35a39353700b20"},{"type":"text","text":"Lỗi CORS — BE trên production không cho phép origin của FE. Kiểm tra CORS config:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_81z9u5akohki_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"cors\\|CORS\\|allowedOrigins\\|Access-Control\" --include=\"*.ts\" -i | grep -v node_modules | head -20","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":325,"output":344,"cacheRead":10789,"cacheWrite":136612,"totalTokens":148070,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776064145852,"responseId":"062bc9937594fe2cc210b763ea5a3675"}}
